{"TopicId":144481,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Vessels spinning out of control","CreatedByName":"ludan02","CreatedById":166880,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T21:00:53Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ludan02","CreatedById":166880,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T21:00:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhenever I switch to my space station, it starts abruptly spinning, despite me not touching the keyboard whatsoever. Even after time-warping, the space station still\u00A0starts spinning for no reason again.\u00A0The \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E are both enabled, and the space station has reaction wheels and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters. I have restarted the game twice and still nothing is fixing this.\u00A0Any advice would be appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Papa_Joe","CreatedById":10788,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T02:14:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222689583\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469394053\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ludan02\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, ludan02 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhenever I switch to my space station, it starts abruptly spinning, despite me not touching the keyboard whatsoever. Even after time-warping, the space station still\u00A0starts spinning for no reason again.\u00A0The \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E are both enabled, and the space station has reaction wheels and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters. I have restarted the game twice and still nothing is fixing this.\u00A0Any advice would be appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have found that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0can actually exacerbate the problem. \u00A0Turn off your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E and see if the space station settles down after a restart\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Violent Jeb","CreatedById":130681,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T15:43:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[redacted, done contributing]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-16T14:26:32Z\u0022 title=\u002208/16/2016 02:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Violent Jeb\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nansuchao","CreatedById":135151,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T20:03:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had a similar issue on a station that had more than one \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E module perpendicular to each other. One was on the main body of the station the other on a side module. I solved deactivating the side \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ludan02","CreatedById":166880,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-27T22:16:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222689877\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469412873\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210788\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Papa_Joe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/24/2016 at 10:14 PM, Papa_Joe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have found that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0can actually exacerbate the problem. \u00A0Turn off your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and see if the space station settles down after a restart\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTurning off \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E slowed down the spinning a little, but it didn\u0027t completely stop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222690445\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469461421\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130681\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Violent Jeb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/25/2016 at 11:43 AM, Violent Jeb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you accidentally applied some trim? I do this from time to time. Try hitting mod-x (alt-x in my case) to reset trim and see if that fixes it (you can also see if trim is being applied because your indicator in the bottom right will show a rotational torque (not in the middle)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf not this then I have no idea\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried turning off the trim, and it\u00A0didn\u0027t\u00A0work\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222690785\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469477018\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135151\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nansuchao\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/25/2016 at 4:03 PM, Nansuchao said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had a similar issue on a station that had more than one \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E module perpendicular to each other. One was on the main body of the station the other on a side module. I solved deactivating the side \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy station does have perpendicular reaction wheels, but disengaging the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E still didn\u0027t stop the spinning \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry about the late replies BTW, I\u0027ve been kinda busy this week\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Papa_Joe","CreatedById":10788,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-27T22:48:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it slowed down the spinning, then \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E was likely the issue... you may need to apply some small counterthrust to completely stop it... a body in motion tends to stay in motion...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe trick will be when and were to apply... you can just make it worse if not properly applied\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-27T22:48:47Z\u0022 title=\u002207/27/2016 10:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Papa_Joe\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ludan02","CreatedById":166880,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T16:39:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222693902\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469659688\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210788\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Papa_Joe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Papa_Joe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it slowed down the spinning, then \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E was likely the issue... you may need to apply some small counterthrust to completely stop it... a body in motion tends to stay in motion...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe trick will be when and were to apply... you can just make it worse if not properly applied\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt worked! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0Now if only I could find out why the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is causing this...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Papa_Joe","CreatedById":10788,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T17:21:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222694758\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469723972\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ludan02\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n46 minutes ago, ludan02 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt worked! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0Now if only I could find out why the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is causing this...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcellent. \u00A0It is a relic of the past... \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E has been an issue in game for years. \u00A0As \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/135151-nansuchao/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022135151\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/135151-nansuchao/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Nansuchao\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, perpendicular \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E will fight with each other, and create torsional forces on your space station. \u00A0 Think of it like this. \u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is a reactional activity, based on relative motion. \u00A0so you experience an affect called \u0022chasing the ball\u0022 used by\u00A0flight instructors to denote novice pilots\u00A0trying to stay at\u00A0a given altitude by reacting to the altimeter, instead of anticipating it. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve built\u00A0maybe a dozen stations or so.. .some pretty large, across several planets (yes, the hard way, not via hyperedit \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E ), and I had experienced these issues also... so as a rule I now leave \u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E off for stations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-28T17:26:56Z\u0022 title=\u002207/28/2016 05:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Papa_Joe\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ludan02","CreatedById":166880,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T19:39:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222694816\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469726518\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210788\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Papa_Joe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Papa_Joe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcellent. \u00A0It is a relic of the past... \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E has been an issue in game for years. \u00A0As \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/135151-nansuchao/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022135151\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/135151-nansuchao/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Nansuchao\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, perpendicular \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E will fight with each other, and create torsional forces on your space station. \u00A0 Think of it like this. \u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is a reactional activity, based on relative motion. \u00A0so you experience an affect called \u0022chasing the ball\u0022 used by\u00A0flight instructors to denote novice pilots\u00A0trying to stay at\u00A0a given altitude by reacting to the altimeter, instead of anticipating it. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve built\u00A0maybe a dozen stations or so.. .some pretty large, across several planets (yes, the hard way, not via hyperedit \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E ), and I had experienced these issues also... so as a rule I now leave \u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E off for stations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-size:16px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003ESo it turns out the problem was trim, but KSP was ignoring Alt\u002BX and it didn\u0027t reset. The\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E was exacerbating\u00A0the problem though, and I\u0027ll follow your advice and keep it off on stations in the future.\u00A0Thanks for the help!\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}